Richard de Buckby was taken with a tapet stolen in Nottingham‚ in the house of Thomas Lucas of Nottingham, and he is arraigned at the suit of the said Thomas, and at this Court‚ as to how he will be acquitted of the said theft ; he says by a good inquest of the town of Nottingham: who come, and say, upon their oath‚ that he stole the said tapet, to wit [one] valued at 7d.
